Section 1:
Act 125 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H1/30/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1048
4
5 By: Representatives C. Cooper, Long, Bentley, A. Brown, Lundstrum, B. McKenzie, Puryear
6 By: Senators A. Clark, J. Dotson
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE INCIDENTAL
10 SALE OF GOAT MILK, SHEEP MILK, AND WHOLE MILK THAT
11 HAS NOT BEEN PASTEURIZED; TO CLARIFY THAT THE
12 INCIDENTAL SALE OF RAW MILK IS NOT LIMITED TO A SALE
13 ON THE FARM; AND OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE
18 INCIDENTAL SALE OF GOAT MILK, SHEEP
19 MILK, AND WHOLE MILK THAT HAS NOT BEEN
20 PASTEURIZED; AND TO CLARIFY THAT THE
21 INCIDENTAL SALE OF RAW MILK IS NOT
22 LIMITED TO A SALE ON THE FARM.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 20-59-248(b), concerning the incidental
27 sale or advertising of raw goat milk, raw sheep milk, and whole milk that has
28 not been pasteurized directly to consumers at the farm, is amended to read as
29 follows:
30 (b) This subchapter does not:
31 (1) Prohibit prohibit incidental sales of raw goat milk, raw
32 sheep milk, and whole milk that has not been pasteurized directly to
33 consumers:
34 (A) At at the farm where the milk is produced;
35 (B) At a farmer's market; or
36 (C) Via delivery from the farm where the milk is produced;
*JMB101*
01-30-2025 09:43:57 JMB101
As Engrossed: H1/30/25 HB1048
1 or
2 (2) Preclude preclude the advertising of incidental sales of
3 goat milk, sheep milk, and whole milk that has not been pasteurized.
4
